Gordon Brisker (November 6, 1937 in Cincinnati, Ohio – September 10, 2004) was an American jazz tenor saxophonist.

From 1983 to 1985, Brisker taught at Berklee, and during this time also arranged for Herb Pomeroy; after 1985 he returned to Los Angeles.

In the 1990s, Brisker moved to Australia and taught at the Sydney Conservatorium of Music.
Brisker died of pancreatic cancer on September 10, 2004, at the age of 66.
